<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../partials/head'); %>
  <style>
    .jumbotron {
      padding-left: auto;
      padding-right: auto;
      padding-top: 5em;
      max-width: 1024px;
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5em;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.8em;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    h3 {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    ul {
      list-style-type: disc;
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }
    .center-in-place {
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }
    .dont-section li {
      display: list-item;
      list-style-type: "‚ùå";
      padding-inline-start: 1ch;
    }
    .do-section li {
      display: list-item;
      list-style-type: "‚úÖ";
      padding-inline-start: 1ch;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <%- include('../partials/header'); %>
</header>

<script>
    document.getElementById('wildfires-nav-item').classList.add('is-active');
</script>


<main>
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Wildfires</h1>
    <p>Wildfires often start small and are typically caused by lightning, engulfing everything in their path in flames. As people start to expand the regions in which they build homes, wildfires are becoming more frequent throughout the years. It is very important, especially in areas where wildfires are common, to prepare ahead of time.</p>

    <div class="columns pt-3 center-in-place">
      <div class="column p-3">
        <img src="/images/mike-newbry-forest-fire-unsplash.jpg" alt="Wildfire burning on a mountain" width="99%" style="border-radius: 12px; filter: drop-shadow(2px 6px 8px #000000bb)">
        <p class="pt-3" style="color: #cccccc; text-align: center; font-style: italic">Photo by Mike Newbry on Unsplash</p>
      </div>
      <div class="column p-3 pl-5 ml-2">
        <h2>Preparations before wildfire</h2>
        <ul class="pt-2">
          <li>Assemble a <span class="highlighted">disaster kit</span>:
            <ul class="pt-2">
              <li>Water</li>
              <li>Food</li>
              <li>Fire blanket</li>
              <li>Money</li>
              <li>First aid materials:
                <ul class="pt-2">
                  <li>Bandages of many sizes</li>
                  <li>Antibiotic and burn ointments</li>
                  <li>Aspirin and pain relievers</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Have an <span class="highlighted">evacuation plan</span> in place</li>
          <li>Design your home with <span class="highlighted">fire-resistant materials</span> and plants</li>
          <li>Have a <span class="highlighted">fire extinguisher</span> and know how to use it</li>
          <li>Ensure <span class="highlighted">smoke alarms</span> are installed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div> 
    <div class="quiz-section">
      <h3 class="quiz-title">ü§î Quiz Time! Test Your Knowledge</h3>
      <p>What should be in your disaster kit?</p>
      <div class="columns is-multiline">
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Water</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Food</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Flashlight</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">All of these</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="columns pt-3 center-in-place">
      <div class="column p-3">
        <img src="images/marcus-kauffman-unsplash.jpg" alt="Wildfire burning a forest" width="99%" style="border-radius: 12px; filter: drop-shadow(2px 6px 8px #000000bb)">
        <p class="pt-3" style="color: #cccccc; text-align: center; font-style: italic">Photo by Marcus Kauffman on Unsplash</p>
      </div>  
      <div class="column p-3 pl-5 ml-2">
        <h2>What to do during a wildfire</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><span class="highlighted">Evacuate immediately</span> if the situation becomes unsafe, and follow your evacuation plan</li>
          <li>Wear clothing that is <span class="highlighted">protective</span> and <span class="highlighted">limits exposure</span> to smoke</li>
          <li><span class="highlighted">Turn off any natural gas</span> inside the house</li>
          <li>Fill as many nearby trashcans, pools, or bins <span class="highlighted">full of water</span> and soak the house if possible</li>
          <li><span class="highlighted">Close</span> all windows and doors</li>
    
          <li><b>If trapped inside your house:</b>
            <ul class="pt-2">
              <li>Stay inside the <span class="highlighted">middle of the house</span>, away from walls</li>
              <li>Close and lock all doors and windows</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
    
          <li><b>If trapped inside your car:</b>
            <ul class="pt-2">
              <li><span class="highlighted">Do not leave</span> the vehicle</li>
              <li>Roll up all windows</li>
              <li><span class="highlighted">Drive slowly</span> and try to avoid driving through heavy smoke</li>
              <li>If you must park, do so away from any bushes or trees that could catch on fire and <span class="highlighted">turn off</span> the vehicle</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
    
          <li><b>If you are stuck outside:</b>
            <ul class="pt-2">
              <li>Try to find a ditch that you can cover yourself in and <span class="highlighted">shield yourself</span> from the heat</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="quiz-section">
      <h3 class="quiz-title">üéØ Pop Quiz!</h3>
      <p>Where should you go if you get trapped inside your house during a wildfire?</p>
      <div class="columns is-multiline">
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">The roof</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">The middle of the house</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Against the walls</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">None of these</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>What to do after a wildfire</h2>
    <div class="columns">
      <div class="column">
        <h3 style="color: rgb(247, 99, 99); font-weight: bold">DON'T</h3>
        <ul class="dont-section">
          <li>Return home before authorities say that it is safe to do so</li>
          <li>Enter any burnt structure recklessly</li>
          <li>Wear clothing that does not protect you</li>
          <li>Stay in a building that has smoke or embers and disregard their presence</li>
          <li>Let dangerous dust from debris sit around and risk being kicked up</li> 
          <li>Keep trees that have been burnt and could potentially be dangerous to you or others</li>
          <li>Keep food that has been exposed to the heat or fire</li>
          <li>Ignore other disasters that could be happening</li>
      </div>
      <div class="column">
        <h3 style="color: rgb(116, 227, 112); font-weight: bold">DO</h3>
        <ul class="do-section">
          <li>Return home only when authorities say it is safe to do so</li>
          <li>Be cautious before stepping foot into any burnt structure</li>
          <li>Wear protective clothing</li>
          <li>Make sure there is no smoke or embers in the home; if so, leave immediately</li>
          <li>Water down debris to minimize harmful dust particles</li>
          <li>Dispose of any trees that have been burnt in the fire and could potentially be dangerous</li>
          <li>Dispose of any food that had exposure to the heat</li>
          <li>Inform yourself on other disasters and proceed accordingly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>  
    <div class="quiz-section">
      <h3 class="quiz-title">üß™ Knowledge Check!</h3>
      <p>Does a wildfire affect food inside a house?</p>
      <div class="columns is-multiline">
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">Yes</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">No</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Yes, but only ice cream</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Yes, but only in a cupboard</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="quiz-section">
      <h3 class="quiz-title">üî• Final Question!</h3>
      <p>When should you return home after a wildfire?</p>
      <div class="columns is-multiline">
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">Immediately</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Five minutes after the fire disappeared</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">When it looks safe to you</button>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-6">
          <button class="quiz-button" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">When authorities say it is safe to do so</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="jumbotron" id="sources" aria-label="Sources">
    <ol class="px-3">
        <li><a id="source-1" href="https://www.habitat.org/our-work/disaster-response/disaster-preparedness-homeowners/wildfires">Disaster preparedness: Wildfires | Habitat for Humanity. (n.d.). Retrieved October 6, 2024</a></li>
        <li><a id="source-2" href="https://www.redcross.org/about-us/our-work/disaster-relief/wildfire-relief.html">Wildfire relief. Information | American Red Cross. (n.d.).</a></li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  function checkAnswer(button, isCorrect) {
    // Remove previous answers in the same quiz section
    const quizSection = button.closest('.quiz-section');
    const buttons = quizSection.getElementsByClassName('quiz-button');
    
    for (let btn of buttons) {
      if (btn === button) {
        btn.classList.add(isCorrect ? 'correct' : 'wrong');
        btn.disabled = true;
      } else {
        if (isCorrect) {
          btn.disabled = true;
          btn.style.opacity = 0.5;
        }
      }
    }
  }
</script>

</main>

</body>
</html>
